
What it is: Commands to diagnose and view hardware information from the command line.

Key Commands to Learn:

lshw: Lists detailed hardware configuration (run with sudo lshw -short for a summary).

lsblk: Lists all block devices (disks, partitions) - essential for disk management.

df -h: Shows disk space usage on mounted filesystems. The -h makes it "human-readable" (MB, GB).

free -h: Shows available memory (RAM) and swap space.
